  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../us-environmental-protection-agency-epa-and-china-sign-memorandum-cooperation-greenhouse-g">US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and China Sign Memorandum of Cooperation on Greenhouse Gas Inventories</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 20, 2009</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>There is finally <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/11/18/AR2009111803058.html">a story on page A12</a> of the Washington Post on what is probably one of the most important agreements signed during the President‚Äôs recent visit to China ‚Äî an agreement for the US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to work with China‚Äôs National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC), and specifically NDRC‚Äôs Energy Research Institute (ERI) on greenhouse gas inventories.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../us-environmental-protection-agency-epa-and-china-sign-memorandum-cooperation-greenhouse-g">Read More</a></div></span>
