  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../president-obamas-first-trip-asia-engaging-china-climate-change">President Obama‚Äôs First Trip to Asia: Engaging with China on Climate Change</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 12, 2009</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>As Asia looks forward to President Obama‚Äôs trip, China is seeing important clean energy projects on an almost daily basis.  Not only do we expect new projects from the President‚Äôs trip, but the Asian Development Bank launched a new carbon capture and storage project, and China is looking to buy U.S. solar panels for a new solar base.</p>

<p>With President Obama‚Äôs arrival in Asia just days away, the Chinese press is being upbeat but offering little specific on expectations.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../president-obamas-first-trip-asia-engaging-china-climate-change">Read More</a></div></span>
