  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../big-international-renewable-projects-‚%2580%2593-wave-future">Big International Renewable Projects ‚Äì the Wave of the Future?</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 12, 2009</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>After reading more criticism of the use of <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=20601080&amp;sid=a3sGCD6uuJN8">U.S. funds for a Chinese-financed wind farm in Texas</a>, I was struck by a posting on <a href="http://switchboard.nrdc.org/blogs/bfinamore/empowering_the_us_and_china_th.html">Natural Resources Defense Council China Director Barbara Finamore‚Äôs blog</a> about an enormous project using U.S. equipment in China.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../big-international-renewable-projects-‚%2580%2593-wave-future">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
